Edit platform/plugin-sdk/src/index.ts. The current PromptDefinition (lines 71-101) has:
- arguments?: PromptArgument[]
- render: (args: Record<string, string>) => Promise<PromptMessage[]>

Add a generic version:
```typescript
interface PromptDefinition<TArgs extends z.ZodObject<z.ZodRawShape> = z.ZodObject<z.ZodRawShape>> {
  name: string;
  description: string;
  args?: TArgs;
  arguments?: PromptArgument[];  // kept for backward compat and metadata
  render: (args: TArgs extends z.ZodObject<z.ZodRawShape> ? z.infer<TArgs> : Record<string, string>) => Promise<PromptMessage[]>;
}
```

Update definePrompt to be generic:
```typescript
const definePrompt = <TArgs extends z.ZodObject<z.ZodRawShape>>(config: PromptDefinition<TArgs>): PromptDefinition<TArgs> => config;
```

When args schema is provided, the build command can auto-generate the 'arguments' metadata from the schema (extracting field names, descriptions from .describe()).

Also update platform/plugin-tools/src/commands/build.ts generatePromptsManifest to extract argument metadata from the Zod schema if present.

Update the e2e-test plugin's prompt to use the new pattern as a proof of concept.

Edit platform/plugin-sdk/src/errors.ts. The factory methods (lines 40-68) currently hardcode the error code:

```typescript
static auth(message: string): ToolError {
  return new ToolError(message, 'AUTH_ERROR', { category: 'auth' });
}
```

Change each to accept optional code:
```typescript
static auth(message: string, code?: string): ToolError {
  return new ToolError(message, code ?? 'AUTH_ERROR', { category: 'auth' });
}
```

Apply the same pattern to: auth, rateLimited, validation, timeout, internal. notFound already has this pattern. Ensure the type signature is consistent across all factories.

